perfcenter.baseclass

Class ModelParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • perfcenter.baseclass.ModelParameters

  • public class ModelParameters
extends java.lang.Object
    All model input parameters in one class. This class is also used to keep some intermediate variables.

    akhila

    • Field Detail

      • solutionMethod

        static SolutionMethod solutionMethod
        Method of solving the distributed system's layered queueing network. This can be simulation or analytical.

      • systemType

        private static SystemType systemType
        System type is the nature of the workload in the system. This can be open or closed. The current workload details does not allow mixing both of these modes, but in simulation mode this can be implemented in future.

      • warnings

        private static Warnings warnings
        Decides whether to validate the system for undeployed hosts / servers before solving it. A value of DISABLE would switch off this checking.

      • numberOfUsers

        private static Variable numberOfUsers
        Total number of users / requests in a closed system, either being processed, or waiting, or thinking.

      • arrivalRate

        public static Variable arrivalRate
        Arrival rate to the system, in case of open system.

      • thinkTime

        private static Distribution thinkTime
        Time for which the requests think. This is essentially outside the system. This is used to determine when to generate the next request when one request exists the system.

      • timeout

        private static Distribution timeout
        Timeout value indicates the time after which end-user would stop waiting for the reply. Since the user would stop waiting, any processing done beyond this time is considered bad. This is essential in computing the badput, goodput etc of the system.

      • retryProbabilty

        private static Variable retryProbabilty
        Probability with which the user would send the same request back to the system, as a retry attempt after timing out. When a request times out, the user can choose to just leave, and not issue the request again, or the request can be reissued for re-processing. This variable is the probability of retrying and sending the request again.

      • outputFileString

        static java.lang.String outputFileString
        Output would be redirected to this file also. This does not work for all classes, and needs some improvement in the way its implemented. Low priority. Way-around is to get all the output on the console and manually redirecting it to a file.

      • totalNumberOfRequests

        private static double totalNumberOfRequests
        Total number of requests which will be simulated. If not specified, this defaults to 10000;

      • simulationEndTime

        private static Variable simulationEndTime
        Time for which the simulation should be run. This parameter is considered if and only if the total number of requests are not specified in the input file. Its value defaults to 100 time units.

      • totalNumberOfRequestEnabled

        private static boolean totalNumberOfRequestEnabled
        Flag indicating if input file specified the total number of requests. Defaults to false.

      • simulationEndTimeEnabled

        private static boolean simulationEndTimeEnabled
        Flag indicating if input file specified the total time to run simulation. Defaults to false.

      • confIntervalsEnabled

        static boolean confIntervalsEnabled
        Flag indicating if confidence intervals are enabled in the input. Defaults to false.

      • numberOfReplications

        private static double numberOfReplications
        Number of replications to run if the confidence interval is true. Defaults to 1.

      • startUpSampleNumber

        private static double startUpSampleNumber
        Total number of requests to be considered in warm-up phase. This is considered only if the total number of requests is specified in the input file.

      • coolDownSampleNumber

        private static double coolDownSampleNumber
        Total number of requests to be considered in the warm-down phase. This is considered only if the total number of requests is specified in the input file.

      • qlenCILevel

        private static double qlenCILevel
        Confidence interval level of queue length metric. Defaults to 0.95.

      • utilCILevel

        private static double utilCILevel
        Confidence interval level of utilization metric. Defaults to 0.95.

      • tputCILevel

        private static double tputCILevel
        Confidence interval level of throughput metric. Defaults to 0.95.

      • resptCILevel

        private static double resptCILevel
        Confidence interval level of response time metric. Defaults to 0.95.

      • maxUsers

        private static double maxUsers
        Maximum number of users in the cyclic workload load specification. This is used by request generation logic to reuse the old requests.

      • maxRetry

        private static Variable maxRetry
        Maximum number of retries that a user might do, before she would give up irrespective of the retry probability. This defaults to 5.

      • isModified

        Flags used to indicate if system is modified since last solution.
